            "en": "An unnamed Imam (either al-Baqir or al-Sadiq) interprets Quran 2:167 as referring to one who accumulates wealth but fails to spend it charitably. Upon death, his heir uses the same wealth for righteous deeds. The original earner then witnesses his own efforts yielding rewards in another person's balance on the Day of Judgment -- a source of anguish and regret.",
